<component name="MDSPlusFieldReader" category="Readers">
  <overview>
    <authors>
      <author>ARSanderson</author>
    </authors>
    <summary>
      <p>
The MDSPlusFieldReader connects to an MDSPlus server and retrieves the
data specified by in the GUI. Currently this reader is a prototype for
a more general reader.
      </p>
    </summary>
    <description>
      <p>
The MDSPlusFieldReader connects to an MDSPlus server and retrieves the
data specified by in the GUI. Currently this reader is a prototype for
a more general reader.
      </p>

<p>The following data fields can be read in by the module, Pressure,
Magnetic Field, Velosity, and Current. The Server, Tree, and Shot must
first be specified. It is possible to select which part of the data to
retireve, either the Realspace or the Imaginary. If the Imaginary is
selected it is then possible to select which mode, 0, 1, 2, or a
sum. Finally one or more fields may be selected.</p>
    </description>
  </overview>
  <implementation>
  </implementation>
  <io>
    <inputs lastportdynamic="no">
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
      <port>
	<name>Output Pressure Field</name>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Field</datatype>
      </port>
      <port>
	<name>Output B Field</name>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Field</datatype>
      </port>
      <port>
	<name>Output V Field</name>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Field</datatype>
      </port>
      <port>
	<name>Output J Field</name>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Field</datatype>
      </port>
    </outputs>
  </io>
  <gui>
    <parameter>
      <widget>Label</widget>
      <label>Autogenerated GUI explanation</label>
    </parameter>
  </gui>
  <testing>
  </testing>
</component>

